entry.content:
sentinel file.



This is done by writing the attestation list version to the sentinel

file content when creating the sentinel file. Next time when parsing

is aborted due to the sentinel file, the version is read from its

content and reported to a histogram. The version string is converted

to an integer which is recorded to a sparse histogram.



This histogram will help us investigate the root cause for the high

percentage of parsings being aborted due to sentinel file.

entry.title: Revert "[ios] Move the logic to select API to SnapshotGenerator"
entry.content:
This reverts commit a7a77903add76f057d79c002c663fd95b31a3c85.



Reason for revert: This caused the issue crbug.com/1514555 because

calling `[self updateSnapshotStorageWithImage:image];` in

`updateUIViewSnapshotWithCompletion:` is wrapped by a callback

and is deferred by posting a task. It delays to update the snapshot

storage. The old image is used when the storage is not updated yet.



Original change's description:

> [ios] Move the logic to select API to SnapshotGenerator

>

> This CL moves the logic to select which APIs should be used for

> taking snapshot images from

> SnapshotTabHelper::UpdateSnapshotWithCallback to SnapshotGenerator.

> The callers of SnapshotGenerator don't have to take care of which

> APIs are used.

>

> Bug: 1485474

> Change-Id: I26698acc9c33cd4e822cf47b7a227f5b70306db1

> Reviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/5145109

> Code-Coverage: findit-for-me@appspot.gserviceaccount.com

> Commit-Queue: Asami Doi

> Cr-Commit-Position: refs/heads/main@{#1240507}

entry.title: CCA: simplify ResultSaver interface
entry.content:
The `startSaveVideo` method is currently only used by video capture in

normal / intent mode, but is not used by time lapse recording. But the

`finishSaveVideo` accepts a `TimeLapseSaver` which makes the interface

looks quite weird.



Since there's not much use of unifying the "create video saver" code

path now, move the create part directly into `Camera` / `CameraIntent`

class instead, and rename the `finishSaveVideo` to just `saveVideo` for

consistency with the other two methods.



Also change the signature of the `saveVideo` to just accept the

`FileAccessEntry` directly instead of having it accept the ad-hoc type

`VideoSaver|TimeLapseSaver`.

entry.title: Improve LoginHandler (Part 7 / N)
entry.content:
This CL is mostly a refactor. It has a slight behavior change that

should not be noticeable to users.



(1) This CL moves logic for checking for prerender from LoginHandler to

HttpAuthCoordinator. This is a refactor and has no behavior change.



(2) This CL deletes logic that cancelled the http auth dialog if the

password manager was not available. This was added 9 years ago at

https://codereview.chromium.org/8741019/ due to a NOTREACHED seen in the

wild that could not be reproduced or otherwise diagnosed. In the current

code, this check does not make sense, as it's already possible to show

the http auth dialog without a password manager. Instead, this CL adds a

new check which is both necessary and sufficient for being able to show

an http auth dialog.

entry.title: [Product excellence] Fix misalignment issue in SE Settings page
entry.content:
Please check b/317141209 for screenshots:

- Comment #2: status quo - misalignment with higher zoom levels

- Comment #3: before (more status quo screenshots) and after the CL



**The problem**



Status quo before the CL uses flex layout per row, which can't guarantee

that header row and other rows will have the same horizontal spacing.



The issue is not as obvious when you no zoom is applied

(https://screenshot.googleplex.com/C9kZ4BkHQfwXidD), because the

column with the controls size similar to the controls shown, so it's not

as noticeable even if you get a few pixels difference. However, when you

apply zoom, you see the header for the second column very misaligned

with the rest of the table.



The problem became much more obvious when we changed the controls for

site search created by policy. Rows on the same table can now have

different controls on the last column, completely breaking alignment

between data rows (https://screenshot.googleplex.com/7oygw7uu6ysLnz9).



**The solution**



We are fixing it by making splitting each table row into two sections:

- Assume table has always 3 columns:

- "name"

- "shortcut" or "url"

- "controls"

- Split columns into two groups:

- First column for "name" is its own group and takes 33% of horizontal

space

- Second group contains the last two columns and takes 66% of

horizontal space

- Second group uses flex layout to align second column on the left and

third column on the right



The solution is not resilient to adding a 4th column to the table, but

I think that's reasonable compromise:

- We have not added columns to that table for many years, there is no

obvious reason why we would do that now

- Status quo is also not resilient, and a new column would simply make

the problem worse than it is today

entry.title: [iOS] Show download progress for Save to Drive
entry.content:
This CL updates Download manager UI code to behave differently when the

current download task has been "added" to Save to Drive.

1. The Download manager view displays a Drive icon when the downloaded

file destination is Drive, and it displays the user email of the

destination Drive account. The progress indicator shows 50% when the

download part is finished, since the upload part i.e. the remaining

50% has yet to be performed.

2. The Download manager state, which used to map almost perfectly to

the current download task's state, now differs upon completion of the

download task: if the downloaded file will be saved to Drive, then

the Download manager state stays "in progress" as long as the upload

is not complete. This means the UI stays stuck "in progress" at 50%

when the download finishes, in the Drive case.

3. The downloaded file is not moved to the "Downloads" folder on local

storage if the downloaded file will be saved to Drive.
